1. Install the libraries
   https://fontawesome.com/v5.15/how-to-use/on-the-web/using-with/react

$ npm install --save @fortawesome/fontawesome-svg-core @fortawesome/react-fontawesome

These are installed depending on which subset your icon belongs to:
npm install --save @fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons // only for solid icons
npm install --save @fortawesome/free-regular-svg-icons // only for regular icon
npm install --save @fortawesome/free-brands-svg-icons // for brands

2. Add individual icons
   https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-font-awesome-5-with-react

In your component file:

// This enables using the FontAwesomeIcon component
import { FontAwesomeIcon } from "@fortawesome/react-fontawesome";

// If your Fontawesome class is "fab fa-github", that means it is "brand"("b"); turn the second part it into lowerCamel:
import { faGithub } from "@fortawesome/free-brands-svg-icons"

Then in the component function:
<FontAwesomeIcon icon={faGithub} />
